article.description: — B.J. Mack scored 24 points, Austin Patterson scored 20 — both career highs — and Wofford easily defeated Kennesaw State 88-62 on Sunday.
article.headline: Mack, Patterson lead Wofford past Kennesaw State 88-62
article.linkText: Mack, Patterson lead Wofford past Kennesaw State 88-62
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- — B.J. Mack scored 24 points, Austin Patterson scored 20 — both career highs — and Wofford easily defeated Kennesaw State 88-62 on Sunday. Mack hit 9 of 12 shots while Patterson made 6 of 9 including five 3-pointers. Max Klesmit had 13 points for Wofford (6-3). Chris Youngblood had 20 points and six rebounds for the Owls (3-6). Spencer Rodgers added 12 points. Kasen Jennings had 11 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
